The {vroom} package has been out for a while now and in this post, we will be comparing it to the {readr} package. Both packages are used to load data in R. Today, weâ€™ll be looking at the time it takes vroom() from the vroom package to load data and comparing it to the read_csv() function from the {readr} package. The {readr} package is part of the {tidyverse} ecosystem.
Who knows, you might learn something from my codes ðŸ¤ª
